text:
West 50th Street, north side, east from Rockefeller Plaza. Shown under construction between Rockefeller Plaza and Fifth Ave., is the 45-story International Building, with its two 9-story Fifth Ave. Entrances. Across the skeleton frame work appears the twin spires of St. Patrick's Cathedral and the ornate tower of the General Electric Building.

October 19, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
